.ident	"@(#)proto:locale/C/menus/help/dtyear	1.7"
.related kbhelp genhelp datetime
.title Help: Date and Time
ABOUT THE DATE AND TIME MENU
Use this menu to check that the current date and time are set
on your computer and to change them if necessary.  You can
also select the appropriate timezone.

CHANGING THE DATE AND TIME
Use the <Tab> or arrow keys to move to the field (Year, Month, Day,
Hour, or Minute) to be changed; then type the correct information.

YEAR
Use a 2-digit number for the current year (94 for 1994).
At the beginning of a new century, this number is 00.
                                   (CONTINUED)
.page
EXITING THE DATE AND TIME MENU
Press <F10> to enter your changes and exit the Date and Time
menu.

EXITING HELP
Press <Esc> to return to the Date and Time menu.
Press <F1> for more help.
